@* Static explainer for the "Which databases can I connect to?" toggle: why only browser-reachable
   databases work, and the current support matrix. Purely presentational — no state, no callbacks. *@

<div class="mb-2">
    <div class="small mb-2">Connections are made <strong>directly from your browser</strong> (no backend), so a database is only usable if it's reachable over <strong>HTTP(S) with CORS</strong> or <strong>WebSocket</strong>. Databases needing a backend proxy will come with the separate server-backed project.</div>
    <table class="table table-sm mb-0" style="font-size: 0.8em;">
        <thead>
            <tr><th>Database</th><th>Language</th><th>Browser transport</th><th>Status</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>TinkerPop — JanusGraph, TinkerGraph, Cosmos DB…</td><td>Gremlin</td><td>WebSocket / HTTP</td><td><span class="badge bg-success">Supported</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td>RDF stores — Fuseki, Blazegraph, GraphDB, Virtuoso; Wikidata / DBpedia</td><td>SPARQL</td><td>HTTP + CORS</td><td><span class="badge bg-success">Supported</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Neo4j, Memgraph</td><td>Cypher</td><td>Bolt over WebSocket</td><td><span class="badge bg-warning text-dark">Planned</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td>ArangoDB, Dgraph</td><td>AQL / DQL</td><td>HTTP + CORS</td><td><span class="badge bg-warning text-dark">Planned</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Amazon Neptune, NebulaGraph</td><td>—</td><td>VPC / binary / no CORS</td><td><span class="badge bg-secondary">Needs backend</span></td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
